id":"3900FB50D9D111EB99FBE1A0D36E44D6","previous_id":1204579,"previous_guid":"37992DF0D9D111EB99FBE1A0D36E44D6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E64D694E32EF4B9091E98D9160C6128F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3. DNA Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D9EAFE392C1C47B99265EFD570A6B0CA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Proceed with the DNA Extraction according to manufacturer\u2019s protocol (Qiagen DNeasy PowerWater kit).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":300,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1204581,"guid":"5D3C7E90D9D111EB99FBE1A0D36E44D6","previous_id":1204580,"previous_guid":"3900FB50D9D111EB99FBE1A0D36E44D6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"548C69C1E0C649928B18F88341A8EF64","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"4. Real-time PCR"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"10C7A98CB05F4926A679C9D3E2769764","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Test DNA extracts for <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">S<\/span><span>. Typhi and <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">S<\/span><span>. Paratyphi A using Taqman-based quantitative real-time PCR (qPCR) platform. <\/span><\/div><br\/><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1221788,"guid":"A300B5B0EE4C11EB80F2A5D531AD487C","previous_id":1204581,"previous_guid":"5D3C7E90D9D111EB99FBE1A0D36E44D6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DDB8FFC481724E4184863DB3BB9B3CF4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"4. Real-time PCR"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"72101493A5E146F7A929067C88D25389","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Detection of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">S<\/span><span>. Typhi<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">S<\/span><span>. Typhi is detected using duplex PCR protocol developed by researchers at the University of Washington (Scott Meschke and team) usIng primers and probes targeting the <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">tviB<\/span><span> and<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> staG<\/span><span> genes (<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/31167843\/\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Nair et al., 2019<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">).<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">tviB<\/span><span>_F 5\u2019TGTGGTAAAGGAACTCGGTAAA-3\u2019; <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">tvi<\/span><span>B_R 5\u2019-GACTTCCGATACCGGGATAATG-3\u2019; <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">tvi<\/span><span>B_P HEX<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">-<\/span><span>TGGATGCCGAAGAGGTAAGACGAGA-BHQ1; <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">sta<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-style:italic;\">G<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">_<\/span><span>F 5\u2019- CGCGAAGTCAGAGTCGACATAG-3\u2019;<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">sta<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-style:italic;\">G<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">_<\/span><span>R 5\u2019-AAGACCTCAACGCCGATCAC-3\u2019; <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">sta<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-style:italic;\">G<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">_<\/span><span>P FAM-5\u2019-CATTTGTTCTGGAGCAGGCTGACGG-3\u2019-BHQ1<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The reaction mixture contain 0.65 \u00b5l of tviB_F (20\u00b5M), 0.75 \u00b5l each of tviB_R (20\u00b5M), staG_F(20\u00b5M), and staG_R (20\u00b5m), 0.5 \u00b5l each of the probe tviB_P (10\u00b5M) and staG_P (10 \u00b5M), 12.5 \u00b5l of SsoAdvanced Universal Probes Supermix (Bio-rad), and 5 \u00b5l of DNA in a final volume of 25 \u00b5l. The PCR reaction conditions include initial denaturation at 95<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C for 5 min, followed by 45 cycles of 95<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C 30 sec, 64<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C 30 sec, 72<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C 10 sec, and final extension at 72<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C for 5 min.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1221789,"guid":"AD79ADD0EE4C11EB80F2A5D531AD487C","previous_id":1221788,"previous_guid":"A300B5B0EE4C11EB80F2A5D531AD487C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"832E79589B62476DA0FA4FD179DE52BE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"4. Real-time PCR"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"481353BAF68D4CF190C3B875AFCBE2DD","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Detection of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">S<\/span><span>. Paratyphi A<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">S<\/span><span>. Paratyphi A Is detected using primers and probe targeting <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">SPA2308 <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/20492644\/\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">(Nga et al., 2010<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">) <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>SPA2308_F<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> 5\u2019-<\/span><span>ACGATGATGACTGATTTATCGAAC-3\u2019; <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">SPA2308_R5\u2019-TGAAAAGATATCTCTCAGAGCTGG-3\u2019; <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>SPA2308_PCY5<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">-<\/span><span>CCCATACAATTTCATTCTTATTGAGAATGCGC-BHQ2 <\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The reaction mixture containing 1 \u00b5l of each primer (10\u00b5M), 0.4 \u00b5l of probe (10\u00b5M), 200\u00b5M of dNTPs, 5mM of MgCl2, 5U of HotStar Taq DNA polymerase (Qiagen), and 5 \u00b5l of DNA in a final reaction volume of 25 \u00b5l. The PCR reaction conditions include initial denaturation at 95<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C for 5 min, followed by 45 cycles of 95<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C 30 sec, 60<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C 30 sec, 72<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C 30 sec, and final extension at 72<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">o<\/span><span>C for 10 min.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The protocol describes method for qualitative detection (presence\/ absence) of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Salmonella<\/span><span> Typhi and <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Salmonella <\/span><span>Paratyphi A in surface water by enrichment culture followed by real-time PCR.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The same protocol can be used for other types of water samples such as drinking water, drain water or flood water.   <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1629742654}